        conseils: "For a journey of nearly 4 hours, plan one or two stops. Avranches (30 km from the Mont) offers a magnificent bay panorama from the Jardin des Plantes and the Scriptorial, a museum of Mont-Saint-Michel's medieval manuscripts. Caen (130 km) is an ideal lunch stop — the Vaugueux quarter has excellent Norman restaurants. If time permits, a detour to the D-Day beaches (Omaha Beach, American cemetery at Colleville-sur-Mer) adds about 1h30 to the total journey but is an unforgettable experience. For arrival in Paris, specify your exact destination (hotel, station, airport) when booking — your driver will optimise the entry point into Paris based on traffic. Sunday evenings and bank holiday returns are the busiest times on the A13; an early morning departure from the Mont avoids Parisian slowdowns. In a van (up to 7 passengers), the per-person cost drops considerably, making this transfer very competitive.",
